headlines.description: — This speaks to how highly the Miami Heat think of Omer Yurtseven. After his finest game as a pro, the Heat told him he's capable of even more.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat win 3rd straight, pull away from Magic 93-83

headlines.description: — Kevin Love and Darius Garland scored 22 points apiece, and the Cleveland Cavaliers tied their franchise record with 46 points in the third quarter of a 144-99 rout over the COVID-19 depleted Toronto Raptors on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Love, Garland score 22 as Cavs rout depleted Raptors 144-99

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 36 points and 13 rebounds and a spat with Montrezl Harrell, Tobias Harris added 23 points and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Washington Wizards 117-96 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid has 36 points and 13 rebounds, 76ers beat Wizards

headlines.description: — Desmond Bane scored 28 points and the Memphis Grizzlies defeated Sacramento for the second time in 10 days, beating the Kings 127-102 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bane, Grizzlies rout Sacramento 127-102, end 3-game skid

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 31 points and rookie Aaron Wiggins added a career-high 24 as the Oklahoma City Thunder beat New Orleans 117-112 Sunday night, snapping the Pelicans’ four-game win streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder beat New Orleans 117-112, end Pelicans' 4-game run

events.name: Detroit Pistons at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Keldon Johnson scored 27 points and the San Antonio Spurs had their highest-scoring game of the season, beating short-handed Detroit 144-109 on Sunday to extend the Pistons’ road skid to 10.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs set season high, blitz short-handed Pistons, 144-109

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 32 points in his return from the NBA's health and safety protocols, DeMar DeRozan added 24 points and the Chicago Bulls beat the Indiana Pacers 113-105 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bulls win 3rd straight game, defeat Pacers 113-105

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic kept the Denver Nuggets from blowing another game with a history-making performance.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has 26 points, 22 rebounds, leads Denver past Clippers
